**Repository for EDS data**

CSV files contain the data for the certified reference materials (files labelled standards) and archaeological samples (file labelled results), separated into their respective files.

Supplemental Figure 4: Frequency distribution histogram showing the normative proportion of anorthite calculated for the feldspar inclusions (n=144) in ceramic fabrics, separated by the ware of the sample. 

Suplpemental Figure 5: Frequency distribution histogram showing the normative proportion of albite calculated for the feldspar inclusions (n=144) in ceramic fabrics, separated by the ware of the sample.

Supplemental Figure 6: Frequency distribution histogram showing the normative proportion of albite calculated for the feldspar inclusions (n=64) in Tuza ceramic fabrics, separated by the individual samples. 

